tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE assembly_line_quality (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  assembly_line_id INT,
  defect_type VARCHAR(255),
  repair_time INT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE line_operators (
  operator_id INT,
  operator_name VARCHAR(50),
  line_id INT,
  shift_start TIMESTAMP,
  shift_end TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE maintenance_logs (
  log_id INT,
  line_id INT,
  maintenance_date DATE,
  maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
  maintenance_description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE assembly_line_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    line_id INT NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    efficiency DECIMAL,
    productivity INT
);

CREATE TABLE defect_tracking (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    line_id INT NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    defect_type VARCHAR(50),
    quantity INT
);

CREATE TABLE machine_status (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    line_id INT NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50),
    maintenance_due DATE
);

CREATE TABLE quality_assurance (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    line_id INT NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    passed BOOLEAN,
    inspector_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE employee_performance (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    employee_id INT NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    efficiency_rating DECIMAL,
    errors INT
);
